postcontent: Blue and color cased hardened with 4? oct bbl, pin front sight and engraved “Saml Colt” address. Left side of the frame is engraved “COLTS PATENT” in a pillow shape. One scroll on the left side of the bbl lug terminates in Mr. Young’s stylized dog’s head and others terminate in flower blossoms. Matching pattern engraving is also on the backstrap, buttstrap and trigger guard. Hammer is deluxe engraved with foliate arabesque patterns on the shank, a wolf’s head on each side of the hammer nose, fish scale patterns on the sides of the spur and top edge with a hand checkered spur. SN’s on the bottom of the revolver and buttstrap are accompanied by a small punch mark which signifies to the polishing room to do extra polishing for engraving. Accompanied by an orig green velvet lined mahogany casing compartmented in the bottom for a double sided eagle and stars pocket sized flask, a brass 2 cavity “COLTS PATENT” mold without sprue cutter and a small cap tin with applied Eley Bros label. CONDITION: Extremely fine, all matching including wedge and grip. Bbl retains 93-95% strong blue with some thinning over the top flats and sharp edges. Rammer and handle retain dark case colors. Frame and hammer also retain dark case colors. Cylinder is a medium brown patina and shows 96-98% stagecoach hold up scene roll marking. Trigger guard and backstrap retain virtually all of their orig silver plating. Buttstrap and bottom edges of the grip are moderately battered. Grip has good edges with light wear and a few nicks and scratches and retains most of its orig varnish. Mechanics are fine, bright shiny bore with a few scattered spots of light rust. Case has 3 or 4 grain checks in the bottom otherwise is sound with usual handling & storage nicks & scratches and overall retains most of its orig varnish. Interior is lightly faded inside the lid, moderately to heavy faded in the bottom. Partitions are solid. Flask is extremely fine retaining 97-98% orig finish. Front forearm can be replaced with Saiga rails and aftermarket forearms. Replacement parts available. Four position gas system. Off, Low, Medium and High. title: For Sale:  Magpul MilSpec STR Stock
postcontent: I'm clearing out old junk to fund new projects, you score some sweet savings on basically new gear, what's not to like? Everyone's happy! Especially my girlfriend, she's getting rather tired of this expensive 'hobby'. Oh well, lets get on...   Per MagpulAR-15 MilSpec Stock - Storage Type, Restricted:https://www.magpul.com/products/str-carbine-stock-mil-specBasically perfect condition, installed once and shot for roughly 200 rounds. Never 'mortared' or butt stroked anything, hasn't even been shot prone off the ground - as you can see from the photos the butt pad is completely fresh.I can confirm that this WILL FIT Vltor A5 buffer tube and fully collapse. I have an A5, it fits almost perfectly flush with the castle nut. This is a MilSpec stock, so if you got duped on a 'bargain' AR and don't know if it'll work, try somewhere else. If you run an AR-10, AK, etc this will also fit if you have an AR-15 tube.The battery tubes in the cheek piece are indeed rattle free with batteries installed, but tragically a .223 boresnake won't quite stuff inside. Fits AA and CR123 batteries, but not 18650s. Magpul was clever enough to include a buffer to stop rattling, but not smart enough to see the coming rechargeable 18650s...The stock itself has a single QD swivel (with limited rotation! Gasp!) as well as slots for traditional two point slings. The friction lock is what sets this version apart from the MOE and other similar stocks like BCM and B5 - it's simply fantastic. It'll lock up tighter than Congress during a filibuster, but snaps right open when you press the lever to adjust length of pull. The weight is good - almost enough to balance out my MedCon 14.5", so a Gov't 16" should be perfect unless you run a suppressor.I'm not looking for much right in the way of trades right now, but PM me and I'll take a look. I will definitely ignore you if your price/trade is a ridiculous low ball, otherwise I respond within a day, usually hours. Willing to meet in the North Atlanta Metro area, anywhere up the 985 corridor, or within a reasonable range thereof. Also happy mailing, if using PayPal you pay the fees/send as gift.

title: For Sale/Trade:  M1933 WW2 German SA Dagger Early model
postcontent: WW2 German SA Dagger pre 1935 maker Christianswerk group stamped Nrh on cross guard. The maker is fairly rare and the Nrh groupe stamp is one of the smallest SA groups. The original production was 7000 and is almost unheard of to find this with the original scabbard. This is the first model dagger with buckle-silver fittings and hand carved and dyed wooden grip. All insignia is in tact and acid etched inscription ALLES FUR DEUTSCHLAND is centered perfectly and stands out beautify against the blade as is the maker mark on the rear of blade. This dagger is made of all the first materials which is the most sought after model SA Dagger since as the war progressed the materials used became cheaper and less details put into craftsmanship. This is a awesome piece of history that has been hiding in a chest in a attic for over 60 years and was brought back as a trophy from the European Theater by a US soldier during WWII. I’m asking for $700 or best offer I have only seen one other with these maker and group marks and it sold for $2100 but was in pristine condition. $700 or best offer any questions feel free to ask. Guaranteed to be authentic and I am fine with any checking over or expert you need to look at it even though once you see in person you can see, feel, and smell the age of the piece. When I worked in the heating and air field I would keep a derringer in my tool bag just for the unexpected opossum whenever I would crawl under a house.
